## 2026-04-04 - bulkRename circular-reference check uses stale flatTokens inside batch
- Fixed the circular-reference check in `bulkRename` which was effectively a no-op: inside `withBatch`, `rebuildFlatTokens()` is deferred, so `this.flatTokens` holds pre-rename state; the old code read new token values from stale flatTokens (always `undefined`) and passed them as overrides, which masked the actual alias-updated dependencies in other sets.
- Extracted DFS logic from `checkCircularReferences` into a new private `runCycleDFS(deps, startPaths)` helper to eliminate duplication.
- Added `buildLiveFlatTokens()` private helper that does a fresh flatten of `this.sets` without the batch depth guard — reflects post-mutation state even inside a batch.

